  "texts": [
    "Returning to the Beth comb of Example 2.18, let us think of the w n as instants of time, the s n as unending stretches of time, and s n+1 as the whole of the future relative to w n. Define an accessibility relation on the Beth comb by: xR < y iff x is the n-th world or stretch of time and y = s n+1.",
    "The result is shown in Figure 2.5, in which successive instants of time peel off of the future.",
    "First observe that if X ∈ RO(S, ⊑), then ■ i X ∈ RO(S, ⊑).",
    "For if X is a regular open set of type (i) in Example 2.18, then ■ < X = ∅, which is regular open; and if X is a regular open set of type (ii) in Example 2.18, then where n = min{k | s k ∈ X}, ■ < X = ↓s n-1, which is a regular open set of type (ii).",
    "Thus, the structure F = ⟨S, ⊑, R <, RO(S, ⊑)⟩ is a full possibility frame."
